Title : Smitley River
Text : The '''Smitley River''' is a [[river]] in the northernmost [[Pacific Ranges]] of the [[Coast Mountains]] in [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], flowing southeast to join the [[Noeick River]] a few miles above its outlet into [[South Bentinck Arm]].  The Smitley begins on the east flank of [[Mount Saugstad]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/21699.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Smitley River"]</ref>

